The DW Course with Harvard University was highly organised, the learning spaces at the Bastow Institute were well thought out, clean and participant seats in the theatre clearly labelled. Other aspects of organisation were finer details such as check in and lunch vouchers, deltas being read and adjusted, resources being ready to use during group times, IT support at the ready, etc. 

In relation to the actual learning and improving educational practice - wow! Thank you, thank you, thank you. I personally feel as though I have gained so much insight into the DWIP and am ready to act and adjust my practice when I begin the 2019 academic year. I already had a 'bigger picture' in some ways of what the DWIP looked like, but now I know the finer details of how to create a full inquiry cycle. Something that I have taken away from this course, apart from the understanding and consolidation of knowledge around being DW is the importance of norms and protocols and celebrating our successes along the way.
